KAIZER Chiefs have extended the stay of midfielder Dumisani Zuma and towering defender Erick Mathoho. Zuma and Mathoho have both penned new three-year deals to add on to their current contracts which are set to expire at the end of the 2019/20 season. MIDDENDORP AND GROBLER WINS PSL MONTHLY AWARDS Chiefs have made no mistake but tie them down as the club is aware that the would have been free agents as of January 2020, from when they could have signed pre-contracts with the club of their choice, before leaving for free. Zuma arrived at Chiefs from Bloemfontein Celtic in 2017 and has been impressive, showing some glimpse of his potential over the past two seasons.   